properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 14 at 3:31AM CST until February 14 at 7:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Strong Winds by This Afternoon in Northwest Iowa...

* WHAT...South winds 25 to 30 mph with a few gusts up to 45 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Portions of northern Iowa.

* WHEN...From noon today to 7 PM this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The strong winds will also produce near
surface blowing snow across roads and highways. Icy spots are
likely to develop on these roadways by this afternoon producing
hazardous travel conditions.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 7 PM CST THIS EVENING
